        "rtf_CVd8LC": {
          "type": "rtf",
          "settings": {
            "richtext_content": "<h1></h1><h3>FAQ's</h3><p><strong>Q: Where can I park?</strong><br/>A: Free parking - Denton Working Men's Club & Institute, 3 Fredrick St, Denton, Manchester, M34 3JB.<br/><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/dir/?api=1&destination=Denton+Working+Men%27s+Club+%26+Institute%2C+3+Fredrick+St%2C+Denton%2C+Manchester%2C+M34+3JB\" target=\"_blank\">Get Directions</a></p><p><strong>Q: How does the points system work?</strong><br/>A: Each discipline contributes points towards the 1,000-point threshold. E.g. 150KG deadlift = 150 points, 100 cals = 100 points.</p><p><strong>Q: Do I need prior experience?</strong><br/>A: Having a good level of fitness is advised, however the Games are designed for athletes of all levels; staff will guide you safely through each challenge.</p><p><strong>Q: Can I attend just to watch?</strong><br/>A: Absolutely. Tickets are required for participation; spectators are welcome to attend.</p><p><strong>Q: How do I redeem my voucher code for Gym King?</strong><br/>A: Your unique code will be included with your ticket confirmation.</p><p><strong>Q: For doubles, is the deadlift score combined or best lift?<br/></strong>A: For doubles, the score is based on the best individual deadlift, not a combined total.<br/>For example, if one partner lifts 100kg and the other lifts 75kg, your score would be 100 points, not 175.</p><p><strong>Q: For doubles, is it 5 minutes each per station or 5 minutes shared?<br/></strong>A: It’s 5 minutes total between both partners.<br/>How you split that time is completely up to you - for example, 2.5 minutes each, alternating sets, or one partner starting and the other finishing.</p><p><strong>Q: What are the wall ball weights and target heights?</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Women:</strong> 4kg ball, 9ft target</li><li><strong>Men:</strong> 6kg ball, 10ft target</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Q: How are press-ups judged?<br/></strong>A: A full press-up is counted when the movement goes from chest to fist.</p><p><strong>Q: How are calories tracked on the machines?<br/></strong>A: Each machine will be reset before every participant.<br/>The total calories burned at the end of each 5-minute station will be recorded, then reset ready for the next competitor.</p><p><strong>Q: Can we use straps or belts for deadlifts?<br/></strong>A:Yes - both straps and belts are allowed.</p><p><strong>Q: How long is each station, and how much rest is there between stations?</strong></p><ul><li>5 minutes per station</li><li>30 seconds transition time between each discipline</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Q: Will Ross be there on the day?<br/></strong>A: Yes - Ross will be there to meet everyone.</p><h3>Safety</h3><p>All participants must complete a waiver prior to entry. Safety and wellbeing are our priorities, and signing the waiver is required for participation in any physical activities.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
